headline: Where Will Applied Materials Stock Be in 1 Year?
summary: The past year has been a somewhat disappointing one for Applied Materials (NASDAQ: AMAT) investors.  Another thing worth noting here is that the capacity for producing advanced chips is expected to grow at a stronger pace of 17%, driven by the production ramp-up of gate-all-around (GAA) chips by the likes of Samsung and Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing.
